<h1>Dropdowns</h1>
<p>
	Dropdowns allow users to select from a list and should be clearly labeled to communicate the content inside it.
	Content inside dropdowns should be grouped by relativity and ranked on importance and/or value to a user.
</p>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-composition">Dropdown composition</h2>
	<p>Dropdown component consists of 3 elements:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>dropdown container (wraps dropdown toggle and dropdown content)</li>
		<li>dropdown toggle</li>
		<li>dropdown content</li>
	</ul>
	{{#component-demo codeOnly=true}}
<div class="wds-dropdown">
	<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">…</div>
	<div class="wds-dropdown__content">…</div>
</div>
	{{/component-demo}}
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-interactions">Interactions</h2>
	<p>
		When user clicks on a dropdown toggle you need to add <code class="format-code">wds-is-active</code>
		class to the parent <code class="format-code">.wds-dropdown</code> element.
		There should be only one dropdown open at any time, so you should also remove this class from all the other dropdowns.
	</p>
</section>

<section>
	<h2 id="dropdowns-default-variant">Default</h2>
	<p>Default dropdown, aligned to left with delicate shadow.</p>
	{{#ds-dropdown}}
	<div class="wds-dropdown wds-is-active">
		<div class="wds-dropdown__toggle">
			<span>Default dropdown aligned to left</span>
			<svg class="wds-icon wds-dropdown__toggle-chevron">
				<use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#wds-icons-dropdown" />
			</svg>
		</div>
		<div class="wds-dropdown__content">
			<ul class="wds-list">
				<li>List item 1</li>
				<li>List item 2</li>
				<li>List item 3</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>
	{{/ds-dropdown}}
